modules.description: Handles parsing and serialization of HTTP cookie strings, including extraction of key-value pairs, domain and path restrictions, and expiration dates. Operates on strings and associative lists representing cookie attributes. Used to process incoming cookies from HTTP headers and generate outgoing Set-Cookie headers.

Sets a cookie with a specified name, value, and optional expiration in days or path. Retrieves a cookie's value by name, returning an option type. Removes a cookie by its name, ensuring it is no longer accessible in subsequent requests.
